<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-01T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="923" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d923">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7732</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-01T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Recent reports from Sonora indicate Yaquis again menacing life and
                            property. Special reference to section La Colorada to Mazatan and San
                            Javier. Request stationing of garrisons Yaqui territory sufficient to
                            afford security against sudden raids.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>